features: Light-Coverage Matte Finishing Powder: Complete your look while adding a matte finish with this light-coverage finishing powder.
Clarifies and Refines: Ingredients like Tea Tree Extract and Witch Hazel help to clarify the skin while reducing redness and the appearance of pores, as it leaves your face feeling fresh and toned.

Skin-Loving Ingredients: Formulated with a nourishing blend of soothing ingredients like Chamomile Extract, Seabuckthorn, Oatmeal, Vegetable Collagen, Eucalyptus Oil, and Vitamin E, this finishing powder helps to soften and condition the skin, while leaving it more hydrated, and looking plumper and more elastic.
For All Skin Types: Whether you have naturally dry, oily, or combination skin, this powder works wonders on any skin type.
Cruelty-Free and Vegan: Wet n Wild makeup products are never tested on animals and are always cruelty-free.
body.description: Achieve radiant polished looks with the help of Wet n Wild’s Bare Focus Clarifying Finishing Powder. Thoughtfully formulated with a nourishing blend of vitamins and revitalizing extracts, this finishing powder is great for all skin types and helps keep makeup looking fresh, while promoting fresher-looking skin. Simply brush it on and enjoy sealed-in looks with a gorgeous matte finish.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I really like the fact that this has witch hazel, tea tree, chamomile, collagen, radish root, oat kernel flour, eucalyptus Leaf oil....so some impressive ingredients. The finishing powder is white and goes on sheer. It's a very small pot so if this is something you use daily it definitely will not last long. It should last me for quite a while though with what I need it for.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Pressed Powder
reviews.reviewText: You don't get much, but the price is right. Also, due to unfortunate genetics, I happen to have pretty big pores in my T-zone, but when I dust this stuff on over my moisturizer, it disguises them enough that I don't need to put on a bunch of make-up to feel comfortable leaving the house to run errands, etc.I have pink undertones in my face, so the light/medium shade isn't ideal for me doing full make-up because it's a bit too yellow. But, for a quick dusting over moisturizer, it's a good no-fuss option for days when I don't want to wear full make-up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Lightweight, slight cast, great for what I need it for
reviews.reviewText: I have bangs and have been looking for a sheer powder product to use on my forehead throughout the day that would not get on the ends of my bangs and discolor them. Although there is an initial cast of white on the face, it absorbs in quickly for me and lasts a few hours. Great for the price and I am very happy with it. It is pretty powdery on the compact when applied with a brush so I would use a sponge or a powder puff :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars LOVE... LOVE IT Great value for money
reviews.reviewText: The wet n wild Bare Focus Clarifying Finishing Powder in Medium-Tan is an absolute game-changer. Its matte finish provides a flawless look, setting my makeup in place for hours without any shine. The pressed powder formula feels lightweight on the skin, giving a natural and comfortable wear. The shade Medium-Tan is a perfect match for my skin tone, providing a subtle warmth without being too overpowering. I love that it clarifies my complexion, leaving a smooth and airbrushed finish. The packaging is not only sleek but also convenient for on-the-go touch-ups. This finishing powder has become a staple in my beauty routine, delivering exceptional quality at an affordable price. Highly recommend for a radiant, matte complexion that lasts all day.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Size Is Much Smaller...😒
reviews.reviewText: Much smaller than I expected. The item weight says 1.27 ounces, which I thought would be bigger than my other pressed powder foundation, but I found out that this is the whole item size including the plastic case, not the actual makeup product size! It's significantly smaller that what I normally get for the same price. I initially got this because the color was slightly lighter than the one I'm using (bc I'm very fair skinned), most makeup products never match my skin tone. 😒 I still haven't found one that actually matches my skin tone. But anyway, as you can see the makeup product itself weight is much smaller than I'm currently getting for the same price. The other reason I wanted to get this was bc the lid snap close feature, it would be easier to take in my purse without the lid coming off or cracking like my other pressed powder makeup. But the depth of the makeup is significantly smaller & the dimension size is also smaller. The makeup is slightly lighter, but not too much of a difference. Look at the pics to compare. The actual makeup size for this Wet n Wild is 0.27 oz. My other makeup is 0.49 oz.
